0 < 0.25$ it becomes\nstronger. We explain the physical meaning of these results, by relating them to\nthe correlation length of the perturbation. Finally, in an Appendix we consider\nthe dipole anisotropy and show that it always leads to weaker constraints.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 1 Aug 1995 14:25:07 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 15 Sep 1995 15:41:05 GMT"}],"update_date":"2008-11-26"}
